@84   = ~Old Diary~
@85   = ~This diary seems to have been written by Firkraag. The first few pages are very old and almost disintegrated. From a few of the remarks, you gain the impression that Firkraag wrote in this diary to enjoy in full the studies of his 'low ones' while in human form. You find a few entries that are interesting to you:

"(...) People are so easy to influence. And, nevertheless, this low form seems to offer some charm. I will prepare an enclave to be able to experiment with it in peace.

(...) I have put a paladin in front of the balancing portal. No matter how much I continue to study him, I do not understand why he does not surrender. He fights and fights... His calls to his God are slowly getting on my nerves. He will probably never figure out that only evil may go through the portal, and that he maintains the balance as the force of good on this side of the portal with his endless fight. I synchronized the portal to him and gave him some aid, so that he will be able to persevere in this fight with his fragile human body. (Just the thought that his strength for this fight does not arise by the grace of his God alone, but also by me, justifies the whole thing.) This involves some risk, considering the self-sacrifice of these fools. However, looking at how resolutely he performs his 'task', I believe I do not have to worry about the overall stability.

(...) One of my experiments seems to be even more successful than I had planned. A girl called 'Sheena' was at the funeral of her mother. How interesting...

(...) Gorion has a fosterchild. A Bhaalspawn! I will attract <PRO_HIMHER> here. This promises to be interesting!

(...) I have fetched more paladins. These fighters for justice are so predictable... It was simple to deceive them, and now they are fooled by even their own senses. It is difficult to recognize one's true enemy if one is surrounded by all-pervasive evil! If it was not so pathetic, one could almost feel sorry for them. But they are insignificant, as my focus lies in attracting <CHARNAME>. Time to see whether my challenge is accepted and how it goes. Garren is, as usual, a toy ball in my hands. I have even included the effigy of the hut of this weakling in my play.

 (...) I will give up the enclave. To monitor <CHARNAME>, and whether and how <PRO_HESHE> would free the paladins out of their loop, will give me a last entertainment. Otherwise, I have lost interest."

The entries end here.
~
