@898  = ~If you ask SIR AJANTIS about his past, he first stresses that he is a paladin of Helm, in service to the Order of the Most Radiant Heart as a knight. He is an offspring of the noble family Ilvastarr of Waterdeep, but due to his marriage with the Bhaalspawn <CHARNAME>, he was disinherited, so now he is called 'Sir Ajantis of Waterdeep'. 
He has learned sword fencing from such luminaries as Myrmith Splendon. Keldorn, a highly respected paladin of the Order, decided to take Ajantis under his wing as a squire. The heroic deeds on the Sword Coast gained Sir Ajantis enough fame and honor to be knighted.~

//TextScreen("c#ajep01")
@899  = ~After the events of the Throne of Bhaal were over, Sir Ajantis returned to his Order of the Radiant Heart, a hero, a savior. With all the prowess he had gained on <CHARNAME>'s side, he fought many battles in the name of good and righteousness, driving fear into many an evildoer of Faerûn. 

Many a young knight wanted to hear the tale about his travels with <CHARNAME>. It was told that when of older age, Sir Ajantis would laugh and say that if he should have been a story teller, Helm would have made him a bard instead.

There is not much knowledge about his private life, but it is said that he did not remain alone, but found a woman he married and proudly shared the name Ilvastarr with. Their marriage was blessed with children, and when coming of age, they, too, wanted to listen to the adventures their father had to tell.

He died of old age, his name eternalized in the bards' tales about the ascension of <CHARNAME>, god of murder.~

//TextScreen("c#ajep02")
@900  = ~After the events of the Throne of Bhaal were over, Sir Ajantis returned to his Order of the Radiant Heart, a hero, a savior. With all the prowess he had gained on <CHARNAME>'s side, he fought many battles in the name of good and righteousness, driving fear into many an evildoer of Faerûn. 

Many a young knight wanted to hear the tale about his travels with <CHARNAME>. It was told that when of older age, Sir Ajantis would laugh and say that if he should have been a story teller, Helm would have made him a bard instead.

He was said to return often to his family in Waterdeep, but never did he found a family of his own. If asked about it, Sir Ajantis would answer sternly, that it should not be for him.

He died of old age, his name eternalized in the bards' tales about his own deeds and on <CHARNAME>'s side.~

//TextScreen("c#ajep03")
@901  = ~Having the quiet time they always yearned for, <CHARNAME> and Sir Ajantis lived their life just as they wanted to. Unbound and unhunted by any evil heritage, they decided which fights they wanted to take on, and they did so with all the might and prowess they acquired during their struggles. They also decided where to settle and when to found a family of their own, which they did as they had always planned.

After several years it was said that, through his sister, Sir Ajantis found a way back to his parents. But never did he and <CHARNAME> stay long in Waterdeep, and never again did he bear the name Ilvastarr.

Shortly before his death, after living a long and faithful life as a husband and knight of the Order of the Radiant Heart, Sir Ajantis called himself the 'happiest man that ever lived, with <CHARNAME>, my love.'~

//TextScreen("c#ajep04")
@902  = ~Having the quiet time they always yearned for, <CHARNAME> and Sir Ajantis now had the time to celebrate their marriage, and they did so. They lived their life just as they wanted to. Unbound and unhunted by any evil heritage, they decided which fights they wanted to take on, and they did so with all the might and prowess they acquired during their struggles. They also decided where to settle and when to found a family of their own, which they did as they had always planned.

After several years it was said that, through his sister, Sir Ajantis found a way back to his parents. But never did he and <CHARNAME> stay long in Waterdeep, and never again did he bear the name Ilvastarr.

Shortly before his death, after living a long and faithful life as a husband and knight of the Order of the Radiant Heart, Sir Ajantis called himself the 'happiest man that ever lived, with <CHARNAME>, my love.'~

//TextScreen("c#ajep05")
@903  = ~After witnessing his betrothed's rise to godhood, Sir Ajantis intensified his fighting for good and righteousness for the Order of the Radiant Heart, driving fear into many an evildoer alongside Faerûn. 

As Helm was his guidance for his fights against evil, <CHARNAME> always remained the goddess of his heart. He lived several years in solitude, fighting and praying to his two gods, but it was said that, through his sister, he finally found a way back to his family in Waterdeep. Words are that his parents offered him a place amongst them once again, and he was henceforth seen to visit them occasionally. But never did he stay long, and never again did he call himself a son of Ilvastarr. 

His last words, passed down by his last squire Sir Kenran, were said to be: 'By Helm... <CHARNAME>, my love.'~

@904  = ~The Righteous, Bastard Sword +3

The name of this Bastard Sword probably stems more from its famous owner than from the properties of the sword. Sir Teuben, Paladin and knight from the far north, with the help of this sword, ended a plague of robbers in the woods near his home town. He fought relentlessly against the robber horde, unaffected by evil spells, and it seemed to many observers as if his vital force increased the longer he held the sword in his hands.
The sword was reforged by Cromwell to hold the magic spell Courage. <CHARNAME>'s imp Cespenar improved the sword's effects.

STATISTICS:
The wielder can cast Courage three times per day.
Equipped Ability :
  Regeneration: 1 hp every 15 seconds
  10% magic resistance.
  Can cast Remove Fear three times per day.

THACO: +2 bonus
Damage: 2D4 + 3
Damage type: slashing
Weight: 7
Speed Factor: 5
Proficiency Type: Bastard Sword
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 11 Strength

Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Cleric
 Mage
 Thief

Creatures of Evil Alignment.~
@905  = ~Ilvastarr Family Shield +4
A medium shield is carried in the same manner as a small shield. Its weight prevents the character from using his shield hand for anything else. Medium shields are usually made of metal, range from 3'-4' in diameter, and can be of any shape, from round to square to a spread dragon's wings. A typical medieval shield resembles a triangle with one point facing downward.

This particular shield bears the coat of arms of the noble Ilvastarr family of Waterdeep: a metallic green dragon with orange eyes on a golden field. The shield's level of armor protection has been improved since Ajantis' time on the Sword Coast. Additionally, the armor class of this shield was increased by Cromwell as well as Cespenar.

STATISTICS:

Armor Class Bonus: 5
Weight: 7
Special:
Grants proficiency in Sword and Shield style while equipped.

Not Usable By:
Creatures of evil alignment.
~

