//Journal entries
//unsolved journal
@10000 = ~Journey to the Windspear Hills.

Ajantis was among the knights of the order I have slain in the Windspear Hills! I just cannot believe he will be lost to me forever.~ 
@10001 = ~Journey to the Windspear Hills.

Ajantis was among the knights of the Order I have slain in the Windspear Hills! I just cannot believe he will be lost to me forever. But something is odd, my god does not turn away from me, even though I have slain innocents. What does that mean?~ 
@10002 = ~Journey to the Windspear Hills.

The knights of the Order took the corpses of the slain paladins to transport them back to the Order. The bodies are unnaturally disfigured by the influence of strong evil magic, and there is probably no hope of saving them.~

@10003 = ~Ajantis' Engagement Ring.

Ajantis would like to have a new engagement ring made for me, and he leaves me the choice of what color the precious stone of the ring should be. Once I have decided, I should inform him, so that he can have the ring made.~ 
@10004 = ~Ajantis' Engagement Ring.

Ajantis would like to get the fragments of the engagement ring from me, in order to forge a new ring out of them. He waits for me to give him the fragments so that he can send them to a goldsmith. ~ 
@10005 = ~Wedding with Ajantis.

Ajantis' parents are in the Mithrest Inn. I should go there with Ajantis to find out whether or not they agree to our engagement.~ 
@10006 = ~Wedding with Ajantis.

Everything is prepared for the wedding. Ajantis and I can go at any time to the temple of Helm that we have selected for the wedding, and priest Antaunus will wait there for us.~
 @10007 = ~Ajantis' Repudiation.

The Ilvastarrs claim back the family shield from Ajantis. Ajantis places great value on the idea that we get it and send it back to the family.~ 
//For translation, please refer to StrRef:16331:
@10008 = ~The Final Battle with Bodhi.

Bodhi appeared in an ambush shortly before I reached her haven, warning me that she was aware of my pursuit and stealing from me the one person that is dearest to my heart: Ajantis. Before she vanished and unleashed more of her undead creations upon me, Bodhi warned me that if I continue, I will lose even more than I thought possible. I cannot give up on the Rhynn Lanthorn... but now the life and immortal soul of the one I love are at stake, as well!~ 
//refer to string #3927 for translation:
@10009 = ~The Final Battle with Bodhi.

Bodhi has turned Ajantis into a vampire!  Or... or very nearly. The process may not have been completed in the short time Bodhi has had him. Hopefully, something can be done, or I will have lost him. Perhaps the elven war sage might know some way of restoration... or Elhan... ~ 
@10010 = ~Ajantis has Fallen!

It seems as though the information in the book of knowledge was correct... Amaunator's symbol has not only returned Ajantis to life, but has also released him from the curse of vampirism. But his actions as a vampire have been sufficient to make a fallen paladin of him! He said that Helm has left him, and he would try to regain Helm's mercy. I can find him in a place where he can be near Helm.~
 @10011 = ~The Golden Globe.

One of Firkraag's underlings gave me a golden globe. He seemed to think this awfully funny. There's something special about this orb. It seems to be quite breakable, so perhaps it reveals its purpose if I destroy it. If I want to learn more about it, however, I'll have to find somebody who can explain what this is all about.~ 
@10012 = ~The Golden Globe.

One of Firkraag's underlings gave me a golden globe. He seemed to think this awfully funny. There's something special about this globe. It seems to be quite breakable, so perhaps it will reveal its purpose if I destroy it. If I want to learn more about it, however, I'll have to find somebody who can explain what this is all about. Firkraag is not able to explain his *jest* to me anymore, after all.~ 
@10013 = ~The Golden Globe.

The abbot in the temple of Oghma was able to tell me the purpose of the globe. According to him, it is a magical portal, which can be activated by throwing the globe on the floor.~ 
@10014 = ~The Golden Globe.

The abbot of Oghma offered to open the portal for me and reverse its direction. I wouldn't have to step through to learn what - or who - awaits me on the other side.~ 
@10015 = ~The Golden Globe.

The golden globe opens a portal. But it seems that it can only be used in the Windspear Hills.~ 
@10016 = ~The Golden Globe.

After stepping through the portal, we found ourselves in some sort of illusion of the Windspear Hills, and again we have been confronted by these knights manifesting as monsters. The situation was completely the same as earlier in the Windspear Hills - until the knights disappeared again before they were able to attack. Now we are stuck in this area, and nothing else remains to be done but to ransack it.~
@10017 = ~The Golden Globe.

As we attempted to enter Garren's cabin in Firkraag's illusion, we arrived again on the Windspear Hills battle scene. It looks like Ajantis and the other knights have been trapped in some sort of time warp. I have to find a way to release them, and I'm afraid talking won't help us in this.~
@10018 = ~The Golden Globe.

As we attempted to enter Garren's cabin in Firkraag's illusion, we arrived again on the Windspear Hills battle scene. It looks like Ajantis and the other knights have been trapped in some sort of time warp. The invisible rune did nothing! Obviously, I'll need more information from Firkraag's minions to learn how to release Ajantis and the other paladins.~ 
@10019 = ~The Golden Globe.
The invisible rune did nothing! Obviously, I'll need more information from Firkraag's minions to learn how to release Ajantis and the other paladins.~ 
@10020 = ~The Golden Globe.

The (now visible) rune worked! The paladins are free and the monstrous illusions dispelled. Now we have to find an exit. The paladins set off to look for a portal.~ 
@10021 = ~The Golden Globe.

The (now visible) rune worked! The paladins are free and the monstrous illusions dispelled. Finally, I am assured that Ajantis is alive. Now we have to find an exit. The paladins set off to look for a portal. Ajantis stayed with them; he may not join me until we have escaped this strange world Firkraag created.~ 
//solved journal

@10022 = ~Wedding with Ajantis.

Ajantis and I are married at last! The wedding took place in the temple of Helm.~ 
@10023 = ~The Golden Globe.

The riddle of Firkraag's 'golden globe' is solved. It was a portal to an enclave that contained a replica of the Windspear Hills. It was there that he kept the paladins imprisoned. I probably earned the gratitude of the Order by freeing them.~ 
@10024 = ~The Golden Globe.

The riddle of Firkraag's 'golden globe' is solved. It was a portal to an enclave that contained a replica of the Windspear Hills. He kept the imprisoned paladins there.~ 
@10025 = ~The Golden Globe.

The riddle of Firkraag's 'golden globe' is solved. It was a portal to an enclave that contained a replica of the Windspear Hills. He kept the imprisoned paladins there, and Ajantis was among them! He's alive!~ 
@10026 = ~The Golden Globe.

The riddle of Firkraag's 'golden globe' is solved. It was a portal to an enclave that contained a replica of the Windspear Hills. He kept the imprisoned paladins there. Well... I may have solved the riddle, but unfortunately I managed to *truly* kill the knights... I shouldn't go near the Order's headquarters anymore.~ 
@10027 = ~Ajantis is alive.

I met Ajantis. He had been trapped on the other side of the portal, along with some other knights of the Order. He offered to accompany me, should I require his help. Until then, he's waiting for me in the Order's headquarters in Athkatla.~

@10028 = ~The Abduction of Lady Elgea.

Ajantis learned about my part in the kidnapping of Lady Elgea, and he was not overly excited about it. He attacked me to 'make me accountable'. I suppose Lady Elgea has been freed already. Returning to that house might not be such a good idea.~

@10029 = ~My relationship with Ajantis. 

My engagement with Ajantis is broken.~
@10030 = ~My relationship with Ajantis. 

My bond with Ajantis is broken, and he left. I doubt I will see him again.~

@10041 = ~My relationship with Ajantis.

Ajantis attacked me, to 'bring me to account'. I had no choice but to kill him!~

@10042 = ~Eila Windspear's Betrothed in Trouble.

We witnessed the arrest of Lord Enderold, betrothed of Garren Windspear's niece, Eila. If we want to speed up the process significantly, we should try to find proof of his innocence. Chief Inspector Brega in the Council Building should be able to tell us more.~
@10043 = ~Eila Windspear's Betrothed in Trouble.

Lord Enderold told us that we should look for Flinn, one of his former guards, who was responsible for the money transfer of the shipload in question. It is very likely he is to be found among the city guards.~
@10044 = ~Eila Windspear's Betrothed in Trouble.

A former servant named Erenal should give us the next clue to Lord Enderold's trouble. As far as Lord Enderold knows, Erenal was hired to a noble family of Athkatla as a servant.~
@10045 = ~Eila Windspear's Betrothed in Trouble.

Flinn told us to search for a servant called Erenal.~
@10046 = ~Eila Windspear's Betrothed in Trouble.

I handed the receipt over to Chief Inspector Brega. Lord Enderold's innocence is therefore proven, and he should be set free soon.~

@10047   = ~Ajantis' Shield Returned

Ajantis' sister sent the Ilvastarr's family shield back to Ajantis. She wrote that his parents wanted to discard it, news that Ajantis was shaken by greatly. But he is not sure this is the real truth, if his parents are what they were. I fear this has to wait until after our search, though, when all this is over.~

@10048 = ~My relationship with Ajantis. 

My alignment turned to evil, and Ajantis ended our bond!~

